{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "More recent approaches focus on adaptive and task-driven communication structures.",
    "For instance, LLM-Blender [91] orchestrates parallel LLM interactions using pairwise ranking, while task-specific partitioning [92], [93] distributes workload and merges outputs via structural aggregation.",
    "Topological innovations such as linear stacking [94], [95] and dynamic DAGs [96] have been applied for improved reasoning.",
    "To automate topology design, DyLAN [44] adaptively configures agent composition, Archon [97] frames collaboration as a hyperparameter optimization problem, and GPTSwarm [75] employs RL to learn interagent connectivity.",
    "State-of-the-art systems such as ADAS [98] and AFlow [99] use LLMs as controllers to explore topological variants through advanced search algorithms.2) Task Orchestration: In IoA systems, effective task orchestration is essential for agents to operate collaboratively and efficiently."
  ],
